<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Albert To Sign With Turner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Marv Albert will sign with Turner Sports, moving  
his return to broadcasting to the national level, The Atlanta 
Journal-Constitution said. 
</P>
<P>
	``All I can say is that we will be making a major talent  
announcement'' today, said Turner Sports vice president Gregg 
Hughes. 
</P>
<P>
	Albert returned to New York's Madison Square Garden Network last  
September as a weeknight anchor. His duties with Turner are 
expected to include the NBA, boxing, the Goodwill Games and the new 
pro football league that is in the planning stages with NBC. 
</P>
<P>
	Albert's last national telecast was the NBA Finals in 1997 with  
NBC. Later that year he was fired by NBC and resigned from MSG 
Network after pleading guilty to biting a former lover during a 
sexual encounter. He has fulfilled the terms of his probation and 
his record has been cleared. 
</P>
<P>
	In his new deal with MSG, Albert was assigned to call a number  
of Knicks games on radio. His first game back was Feb. 8 in the 
Knicks' home opener against Miami. 
</P>
<P>
	His return to broadcasting was well-received in New York and  
Turner obviously expects a similar reaction from viewers 
nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
