<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Barkley Has Successful Knee Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Arthroscopic surgery on Charles Barkley's left  
knee was a success, but the Houston Rockets' leading rebounder 
won't return to action for at least three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	The operation Sunday to repair a partially torn medial meniscus  
in the forward's left knee went as expected, said team physician 
Dr. Walter Lowe. 
</P>
<P>
	He removed between 10 and 15 percent of the cartilage, just as  
the MRI had indicated would be necessary. 
</P>
<P>
	``There were no surprises,'' said Lowe. ``It was a small  
cartilage tear, pretty much exactly how it looked on the MRI. That 
lets you take a deep breath and relax, not any bigger or worse than 
the pictures would have led us to believe.'' 
</P>
<P>
	No additional damage was caused by Barkley's playing two games  
last week. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley's knee was remarkably free of the damage that seemed  
probable for a 255-pound athlete in his 15th NBA season, Lowe said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've seen some of these knees and I thought we would see wear  
and tear with the type of player Charles is and what he weighs,'' 
he said. ``It was pristine from a wear-and-tear standpoint. The 
rest of his knee was completely normal. We don't have to worry 
about little degenerative areas, of wear and tear, holding up the 
rehab. So hopefully, he will be back pretty quickly. 
</P>
<P>
	``I told him he definitely has some good genes there,'' said  
Lowe. ``He just said, `I told you I was special.''' 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley, 35, is the league's leading rebounder at 17.0 per game.  
He initially tried to play through his pain last week and treat the 
problem with rehabilitation and medication. 
</P>
<P>
	However, after discomfort continued and Barkley had trouble even  
bending his leg Saturday, he and the team chose surgery. Lowe and 
Dr. Bruce Moseley performed the surgery at Methodist Hospital in 
Houston. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley had led the Rockets after recovering fully from  
off-season double hernia and elbow surgery. During Houston's 4-1 
start, Barkley averaged 19.2 points and collected at least 15 
rebounds in each game. 
</P>
<P>
	Backup Othella Harrington is expected to absorb most of  
Barkley's minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley's improved conditioning with the season's start will not  
be wasted but would help him return more quickly and effectively, 
said Lowe. The player was to begin rehabilitating his leg today. 
</P>
<P>
	``He wants to return to the form he started this season in,''  
Lowe said. ``He and (personal trainer) Tim Grover were already 
planning a workout. He is intent on proving us wrong on how long it 
will take to come back. This is an injury that definitely could 
respond quickly. He is ready to do the work. I think we'll see him 
back in short order. 
</P>
<P>
	``He still has to recover from the surgery and this injury,''  
the physician said. ``But there is no question he can keep the 
conditioning level where it is. Him coming in in good condition is 
a huge plus here.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
