<HEADLINE> Conn. Girl Dies in Skiing Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VERNON, N.J. (AP) -- A 12-year-old Connecticut girl died Monday  
after skiing off a trail and hitting rocks, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Laura Cournoyer of Seymour, Conn., had been skiing with family  
and friends at the Mountain Creek ski resort. She left the trail 
and struck the rocks at 3:15 p.m., suffering head injuries, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	She was flown to a hospital, where she was pronounced dead.  
</P>
<P>
	Mountain Creek opened on December 24 and Laura's death was the  
resort's first fatality, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Vernon is about 35 miles northwest of Newark in northern New  
Jersey. 
</P>
