</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Grant Hill scored 31 points today, but no one  
else reached double figures for Detroit as the Pistons dropped a 
78-69 decision to the New York Knicks. Allan Houston scored 19 
points, Patrick Ewing had 14, Larry Johnson 12 and Charlie Ward 10 
for the Knicks. 

</P>
