<HEADLINE> Kerry Collins' DWI Case Postponed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- A postponement was granted today in the  
drunken-driving case of former Carolina Panthers quarterback Kerry 
Collins. 
</P>
<P>
	Collins was scheduled to appear in Mecklenburg County District  
Court this morning, but Judge Fritz Y. Mercer Jr. granted a 
continuance. No reason was given and no new court date was 
immediately set. 
</P>
<P>
	Collins, 26, was arrested early on the morning of Nov. 2 after  
police said the car he was driving crossed the center line of a 
downtown Charlotte street. 
</P>
<P>
	His arrest came about nine hours after his new team, the New  
Orleans Saints, lost to the Panthers. Collins was the target of 
repeated taunts from fans throughout the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Collins, the Panthers' first-ever draft pick in 1995, was cut  
last October after reportedly saying his heart was no longer into 
being Carolina's quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
	New Orleans picked him up after his release by Carolina, but the  
Saints said last week that they were not interested in re-signing 
the free agent. 
</P>
