</P>
<P>
	MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Mexico's state-owned oil monopoly Petroleos  
Mexicanos said Monday it had awarded a $1.2 billion contract to a 
consortium to revamp a refinery in the Gulf Coast port of Ciudad 
Madero. 
</P>
<P>
	The consortium led by Mexican construction company Grupo Tribasa  
SA includes Korea's Sunkyong Group and Germany's Siemens AG. 
</P>
<P>
