<HEADLINE> James Brown Endorses Ill. Candidate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Godfather of Soul says he feels good -- about  
Pervis Spann, a candidate for alderman. 
</P>
<P>
	The singer arrived at Spann's South Side campaign headquarters  
in a white stretch limousine Sunday to endorse the candidate, a 
disc jockey and part owner of WVON-AM, as a man who ``understands 
our problems.'' 
</P>
<P>
