<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Spielman May Join Browns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Chris Spielman could soon get his wish and  
become a member of the expansion Cleveland Browns. 
</P>
<P>
	A deal that would send the linebacker from the Buffalo Bills to  
the Browns is in the works and will be announced soon, Columbus 
radio station WTVN and Cleveland radio station WJMI reported Monday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	There was no word from the Browns. A message seeking comment was  
left for team spokesman Alex Martins. 
</P>
<P>
	Spielman, who hasn't played a down in the NFL since 1997, had a  
workout and underwent a physical for the Browns on Friday at the 
team's headquarters in Berea. The Browns were granted permission by 
Buffalo to bring him in. 
</P>
<P>
	Spielman, 33, an Ohio high school star at Massillon who later  
starred at Ohio State, missed half the '97 season with a neck 
injury that required surgery to fuse two vertebrae. He then chose 
to sit out this past year to help take care of his two children 
while his wife, Stefanie, was treated for breast cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	Browns coach Chris Palmer said Monday he was impressed with  
Spielman's workout but otherwise couldn't comment on his chances of 
his playing for the Browns. 
</P>
<P>
	Spielman could not be reached for comment Monday night.  
</P>
<P>
	Last week, he said he would welcome a chance to join the Browns.  
</P>
<P>
	``If Cleveland's the place, that would be great. I'm an Ohio guy  
born and bred,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Spielman has started all 148 NFL games he's played and said he  
wants to remain a starter wherever he's playing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
