<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed in European Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold was also mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.1228, down from $1.1249 on Friday. The  
dollar was quoted at 115.53 Japanese yen, up from 114.25. 
</P>
<P>
	New York markets were closed for the Presidents Day holiday.  
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in London, compared with late Friday: 1.4215  
Swiss francs, up from 1.4194; 1.4936 Canadian dollars, up from 
1.4895. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6261, up from $1.6254.  
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 
</P>
<P>
	--1.7419 German marks, up from 1.7387  
</P>
<P>
	--5.8422 French francs, up from 5.8312  
</P>
<P>
	--1.9627 Dutch guilders, up from 1.9590  
</P>
<P>
	--1,724.50 Italian lire, up from 1,721.28  
</P>
<P>
