<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dave Matthews Honored in Virginia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Even the staid halls of Virginia's Capitol  
are not immune from Dave Matthews mania. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, dozens of girls and boys who work as pages in the  
Senate and House of Delegates rushed through the halls to catch a 
glimpse of the rocker, who was being honored along with the rest of 
the Dave Matthews Band. 
</P>
<P>
	``Oh my God,'' said an awed Mary Reid Ervin, 14. ``I'm so  
excited. I'm just afraid I won't be able to take a picture with him 
because I'm supposed to stand here.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Seconds later, Mary got permission to leave her post to get the  
picture. ``It was so cool,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Grammy award-winning band got its start in Virginia. ``The  
support we've received from all the people in Virginia has made it 
possible to achieve what we have,'' Matthews said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
